# SLDS Lint On Edit

After editing any `.css` or `.html` file, run the SLDS linter on the specific file that was just modified before considering the task complete.

Required command format:

```bash
npx @salesforce-ux/slds-linter@latest lint <changed-file>
```

Requirements:
- Replace `<changed-file>` with the exact path of the file you just edited.
- Run the command once per edited CSS/HTML file to collect lint diagnostics.
- Manually fix reported issues (especially those that are not auto-fixable).
- Re-run lint for each edited CSS/HTML file and do not mark the task done until results are clean (or any remaining issues are explicitly explained).
